results.occurrenceRemarks: There's a funny story to this observation. I could hear this insect's strident call so loud it was hurting my ears and the sharp but heavy "click" it interspersed into it's trill was so percussive I could feel it. But after turning round and round and around again, I still could not pinpoint the right direction; until I realised, from the strength of the vibrations, that it had to be on my hat, which, indeed, is where it was! Photographed in the high grass fields at the top of Victoria Park.
